text: I was at the Bedok Reservoir rustic old town marketplace for a cuppa coffee siewtai (less sugar) when I caught a glimpse of the Reservoir Shopping signage. Plenty of good food, fruit stalls, and sundry goods.

It has everything, from food to household, market, electrical, electronic, fast food! Singapore should always maintain these kind of shops rather than making big malls in heartlands where price has went on spike and unaffordable.

Visited the old siglap kway chap today, delicious!
Kway was silky smooth, intestine was cleaned and fresh, meat was soft and tender, broth was light and drinkable. A very satisfying meal.

MANY MANY MANY STORES ARE CLOSED ON MONDAY!!!!!!!!

Please take note!!!! I came down today (Monday 9am) only to see that maybe only 10% of stalls were open. I did a quick search and saw that many stalls are closed on Mondays and Tuesdays so FYI in case you were thinking of coming here on either day

This shop had big variety of things u chose 4 your home, toiletries; u name it they surely have.
Cashier's Vietnam lady, she polite, pretty n friendly. She assist u get items, if we can't find after searching for sometimes.
